
INHERITANCE:
    1. Inheritance is about deriving the props. from the corresponding parent and grandparents(if any).
    2. This creates a blood relationship b/w classes.


ADVANTAGES:
    1. Code Re-usability.
    2. Polymorphism.

DISADVANTAGES:
    1. Tightly coupled.
    2. Change in parent affects its children.


TYPES OF INHERITANCE:
    1. Single Level.
    2. Multi-level.
    3. Multiple  - Not Supported in Java.
    4. Hybrid - - Not Supported in Java.
    5. Hierarchical - Not Supported in Java.